(2753, 1, '2014-03-25 21:03:38', '2014-03-25 21:03:38', '</font><p></P>[blocknumber type="circle" text="01" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]<font size=12>Always use extra care when handling your lashes.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="02" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Keep them clean. After each use gently remove any lash glue.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="03" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Store in their original packaging to hold their shape and stay bacteria free.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="04" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Remove with care after each wear. To help make the removal easier you can run a damp Q-tip along the band.[/blocknumber]', 'Lash Care Information', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2568-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-03-25 21:03:38', '2014-03-25 21:03:38', '', 2568, 'http://www.femmefatalelashes.com/uncategorized/2568-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2754, 1, '2014-03-21 00:38:56', '2014-03-21 00:38:56', '</font><p></P>[blocknumber type="circle" text="01" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]<font size="3" face="caviar dreams">Always use extra care when handling your lashes.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="02" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]<font size="3" face="caviar dreams">Keep them clean. After each use gently remove any lash glue.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="03" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]<font size="3" face="caviar dreams">Store in their original packaging to hold their shape and stay bacteria free.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="04" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]<font size="3" face="caviar dreams">Remove with care after each wear. To help make the removal easier you can run a damp Q-tip along the band.[/blocknumber]', 'Lash Care Information', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2568-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-21 00:38:56', '2014-03-21 00:38:56', '', 2568, 'http://www.femmefatalelashes.com/uncategorized/2568-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2755, 1, '2014-03-25 21:04:36', '2014-03-25 21:04:36', '<p></p>You want to keep your mink lashes in great condition so you can get the maximum use out of them. Use great care when applying and removing them. For best results apply your lashes after all your makeup has been applied.</font>\r\n<p></P>\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="01" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Gently remove lashes from the packaging and measure them up against your eye. If needed trim from the outside corners so they fit just shorter then the natural length of your eye. [/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="02" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Squeeze a bit of lash glue out onto a clean surface (we love Duo Eye-lash adhesive in clear-white. You can purchase it at Mac Cosmetics).[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="03" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Apply a thin layer of glue to the seam of the lashes. Wait a moment for the glue to become a little tacky.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="04" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Drop the lashes from above as close to your lash line as possible. Use tweezers to adjust them if necessary. Then give them a moment to dry.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="05" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Once both are applied you can gently apply a liquid black liner over your upper lashlines to conceal the seems of the lash strips.[/blocknumber]\r\n\r\n[blocknumber type="circle" text="06" color="#FFF" background="#ff5dba"]Be sure to very gently remove glue and any makeup after each use.[/blocknumber]</font face>', 'How To Apply ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2566-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-03-25 21:04:36', '2014-03-25 21:04:36', '', 2566, 'http://www.femmefatalelashes.com/uncategorized/2566-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
